    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/j0rgbv-09/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=612462104212931091&sectionId=612462104313594387)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggU7cTwtojF_text","label":"ggU7cTwtojF_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">A Guide To Your SerlinoLab Eye Cream</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggBe0DJx3pQ_text","label":"ggBe0DJx3pQ_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">Where to apply it, how much, and why technique matters more than quantity.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg7pGzZg7y3_text","label":"gg7pGzZg7y3_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">How To Use It</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggt5W7ctjdK_text","label":"ggt5W7ctjdK_text","default":"Keep it in the fridge"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9KjE6e4-X_text","label":"gg9KjE6e4-X_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\"><strong>Keep it in the fridge</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggW5doHsOy8_text","label":"ggW5doHsOy8_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">The cold reduces puffiness faster and makes the product more effective. It takes 30 seconds and makes a noticeable difference, especially in the morning.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg1vOTZxWgQ_text","label":"gg1vOTZxWgQ_text","default":"Step 1 — Cleanse first"},{"type":"html","id":"ggQay7_0R18_text","label":"ggQay7_0R18_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 1 — Cleanse first</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg91q9-JyhQ_text","label":"gg91q9-JyhQ_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Always apply to a clean face. The skin around the eye is the thinnest on your entire body — it absorbs everything. Remove residue before you start.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggf683RWjbT_text","label":"ggf683RWjbT_text","default":"Step 2 — Apply"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyciH0gnK2_text","label":"ggyciH0gnK2_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 2 — Apply</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggtMsuzvFc3_text","label":"ggtMsuzvFc3_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Squeeze a tiny amount onto your fingertip — less than a pea. That's enough for both eyes. Dot it along the orbital bone — the curved edge of the eye socket, not the eyelid itself. Never directly under the lash line.</span><br><br>&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Use your ring finger only. It applies the least pressure of any finger. Tap gently in a circle from the inner corner outward, following the bone. Don't rub, don't drag. Pulling the skin around the eye accelerates exactly what you're trying to fix.</span><br><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">More product does not mean better results. It sits on top of the skin and goes to waste. Less, applied correctly, works. More, applied wrong, doesn't.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGtAaYlwRQ_text","label":"ggGtAaYlwRQ_text","default":"Step 3 — Let it absorb"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwFyO5fsZD_text","label":"ggwFyO5fsZD_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 3 — Let it absorb</strong></span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggSvMUldtVE_text","label":"ggSvMUldtVE_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">60 seconds before applying anything else on top. The actives need direct contact with the skin.</span><br><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Use morning, evening, or both.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg50lSKjFA0_text","label":"gg50lSKjFA0_text","default":"<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">What To Expect</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwCdGlY-we_text","label":"ggwCdGlY-we_text","default":"Week 1–2"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnKgtsDXwv_text","label":"ggnKgtsDXwv_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Puffiness reduces. The skin feels firmer. Dark circles don't disappear yet — but the hollow, tired look starts to lift.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPnTyC8Wnw_text","label":"ggPnTyC8Wnw_text","default":"Week 3–4"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLENM_VMAh_text","label":"ggLENM_VMAh_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Fine lines at the corners begin softening. You start looking rested even when you're not.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggAAzj-iPZZ_text","label":"ggAAzj-iPZZ_text","default":"Week 6–8"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOX1w76kcs_text","label":"ggOX1w76kcs_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Dark circles and under-eye hollows visibly reduced. The eye area looks tighter. This is when people around you start noticing — without being able to say why.</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"gggFo5HWShx_text","label":"gggFo5HWShx_text","default":"Month 3+"},{"type":"html","id":"ggeiOwctp3l_text","label":"ggeiOwctp3l_text","default":"<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Structural improvement. One jar was a start. Three months is a real change.</span><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Consistency is everything. Don't run out mid-routine.</span>"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
